YellowBot-API

YellowBot::API is the Perl client for the YellowBot.com HTTP API. The
same platform is used to power weblocal.ca, so with the appropriate
parameters it is also used for that system.

The module requires Moose and LWP::UserAgent (and their prerequisites).


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc YellowBot::API

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=YellowBot-API

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/YellowBot-API

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/YellowBot-API/


